thread.title: Arrieta’s imposing presence has Cubs heading home with smile
thread.title_full: Arrieta’s imposing presence has Cubs heading home with smile | New York Post

author: Kevin Kernan
title: Arrieta’s imposing presence has Cubs heading home with smile
text:
ST. LOUIS — The Cubs now head home on I-55 to Wrigley Field for the next two games of the NLDS, and they are feeling strong because ace Jake Arrieta will go Monday in Game 3. Advantage Cubs.
“You can’t assume anything in baseball, but it’s a good feeling heading home and we have a lot of confidence in Jake,’’ explained his catcher David Ross after the Cubs’ 6-3 win over the Cardinals Saturday night at Busch Stadium evened the NLDS at 1-1.
“I’m really excited, a lot of these guys are excited, the atmosphere at Wrigley, this town has been waiting a few years on this,’’ Ross added. “I haven’t felt their pain, but I feel the excitement around the city of Chicago as you walk around and Jake has been super for us. This game was a must win. My saying around here is we’ve got to have it after a loss and there were a lot of guys saying that to me today.’’
